 \int_{|x|=r}dx=\frac{d}{dr}\int_{|x|<r}dx=\frac{d}{dr}\left(r^n\int_{|x|<1}dx\right)=nr^{n-1}\int_{|x|<1}dx. \tag{1} 
 \int_{|x|=1}dx=n\int_{|x|<1}dx. \tag{2} 
 \int_{|x|=r}dx=r^{n-1}\int_{|x|=1}dx. 
 \int_{|x|=r}dx=\frac{d}{dr}\int_{|x|<r}dx. 
